## Sample Excerpts (for reference)

**Personal / Reflective:**
> "At that point, I refused and sent the nurse away. As a 30 year old man, I didn't want to be s***ing into a bag for the rest of my life. Two days later, a sigmoidoscopy showed my intestine was decaying. Reluctantly, my wife and I made the call."

**Industry Critique:**
> "Stop flooding the industry with endless contract amendments that dwarf the original terms. Respect fair payment terms—28 days from the valuation date. The 'invoice receipt' tactic adds needless delays and pushes real payments to 50+ days."

**Business Reflection:**
> "Back then I priced everything and served as estimator, QS, procurement, admin, contracts manager and everything in between. Thankfully there are far better people in place than me doing these things now."

**Lessons Learned:**
> "I've made many, many mistakes during my career which I'm not afraid or embarrassed to admit, but I've always found one of the most important things is to learn from those mistakes to improve and better yourself."

**Forward Motion:**
> "This is a big change, but the right one for myself. I am excited for the future and incredibly thankful for the journey so far. The story continues, just in a new direction."

